description:
Princess (2014 - Israel)

Drama
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1603900/


4 Award Wins & 6 Award Nominations

This Israeli drama plays out an unsettling scenario of underage sexuality in enigmatic, almost dreamlike terms. Princess follows twelve-year-old Adar, whose relationship with her mother's boyfriend crosses a thin line when their innocent play games turn into a mature relationship. Her mother is a workaholic and knows nothing about what happens at home when she is away. When Adar brings a young boy to her house who looks just like her and as the relationship of the entire family is being tested, it is Adar who soon starts dictating the tone. Artful cinematography and subtle and sensitive performances from the cast help make the case for this emotionally complex drama as being one of the best features at the 2015 Sundance Film Festival.
